SIMPLE: defilement
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Defilement
<hw>De*file"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧filement</ets>. See <er>Defile</er>]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>The protection of the interior walls of a
fortification from an enfilading fire, as by covering them, or by a high
parapet on the exposed side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defilement</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Defilement
<hw>De*file"ment</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From 3d
<er>Defile</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of defiling, or state of being
defiled, whether physically or morally; pollution; foulness; dirtiness;
uncleanness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Defilements</qex> of the flesh.</q>
<rj><qau>Hopkins.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The chaste can not rake into such filth without danger of
<qex>defilement</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Defiler</ent>⟦br⟧
